    <a href="#" class="read-more">Read Full Post</a>
    <div class="full-content">
      <p> In public spaces, it's generally acceptable to photograph crowds and surroundings. However, when photographing individuals, especially close-ups, always seek permission, particularly in sensitive situations or involving children.

        Tourist attractions offer great photo opportunities, but focus on the architecture and surroundings to avoid making anyone uncomfortable. During events and festivals, people may be more open to being photographed, but still, be courteous and mindful of cultural sensitivities.
        
        Respecting privacy extends to private property and street performers. Always ask before taking photos in such contexts. Be cautious when photographing police or security personnel and avoid compromising situations.
        
